summary: April 20 is the 110th day of the year  in the Gregorian calendar.
full_text: Robert Ferdinand Wagner II , usually known as Robert F. Wagner, Jr. served three terms as the mayor of New York City, from 1954 through 1965. When running for his third term, he broke with the Tammany Hall leadership, ending the reign of clubhouse bosses in city politics.
title: Robert F. Wagner, Jr.
